#. <section class="sutta" id="an7.66"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.66:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.66:0.2"
msgid "7. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "7. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 66. Sattasūriyasutta → sattasuriyuggamanasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an7.66:0.3"
msgid "66. Sattasūriyasutta"
msgstr "66. The Seven Suns"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.100"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "an7.66:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "an7.66:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati ambapālivane."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, in Ambapālī’s Wood."

msgctxt "an7.66:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an7.66:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "an7.66:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "an7.66:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an7.66:2.1"
msgid "“Aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā;"
msgstr "“Mendicants, conditions are impermanent."

msgctxt "an7.66:2.2"
msgid "adhuvā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā;"
msgstr "Conditions are unstable."

msgctxt "an7.66:2.3"
msgid "anassāsikā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā."
msgstr "Conditions are unreliable."

msgctxt "an7.66:2.4"
msgid ""
"Yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, alameva sabbasaṅkhāresu nibbindituṃ alaṃ virajjituṃ "
"alaṃ vimuccituṃ."
msgstr ""
"This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and "
"freed regarding all conditions."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an7.66:3.1"
msgid ""
"Sineru, bhikkhave, pabbatarājā caturāsītiyojanasahassāni āyāmena, "
"caturāsītiyojanasahassāni vitthārena, caturāsītiyojanasahassāni mahāsamudde "
"ajjhogāḷho, caturāsītiyojanasahassāni mahāsamuddā accuggato."
msgstr ""
"Sineru, the king of mountains, is 84,000 leagues long and 84,000 leagues "
"wide. It sinks 84,000 leagues below the ocean and rises 84,000 leagues above "
"it."

# BB appears to omit kadaci karahaci etc here, it is in the following sections.
msgctxt "an7.66:3.2"
msgid ""
"Hoti kho so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno accayena "
"bahūni vassāni bahūni vassasatāni bahūni vassasahassāni bahūni "
"vassasatasahassāni devo na vassati."
msgstr ""
"There comes a time when, after a very long period has passed, the rain doesn’"
"t fall. For many years, many hundreds, many thousands, many hundreds of "
"thousands of years no rain falls."

msgctxt "an7.66:3.3"
msgid ""
"Deve kho pana, bhikkhave, avassante ye kecime bījagāmabhūtagāmā "
"osadhitiṇavanappatayo te ussussanti visussanti, na bhavanti."
msgstr ""
"When this happens, the plants and seeds, the herbs, grass, and big trees "
"wither away and dry up, and are no more."

msgctxt "an7.66:3.4"
msgid "Evaṃ aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā;"
msgstr "So impermanent are conditions,"

msgctxt "an7.66:3.5"
msgid "evaṃ adhuvā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā … pe …"
msgstr "so unstable, so unreliable."

msgctxt "an7.66:3.6"
msgid "alaṃ vimuccituṃ. (1)"
msgstr ""
"This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and "
"freed regarding all conditions."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.101"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an7.66:4.1"
msgid ""
"Hoti kho so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno accayena "
"dutiyo sūriyo pātubhavati."
msgstr ""
"There comes a time when, after a very long period has passed, a second sun "
"appears."

#. VAR: kusobbhā → kussubbho (bj) | kussobbhā (s1-3) | kussubbhā (pts1)
msgctxt "an7.66:4.2"
msgid ""
"Dutiyassa, bhikkhave, sūriyassa pātubhāvā yā kāci kunnadiyo kusobbhā tā "
"ussussanti visussanti, na bhavanti."
msgstr ""
"When this happens, the streams and pools wither away and dry up, and are no "
"more."

msgctxt "an7.66:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā … pe …"
msgstr "So impermanent are conditions …"

msgctxt "an7.66:4.4"
msgid "alaṃ vimuccituṃ. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an7.66:5.1"
msgid ""
"Hoti kho so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno accayena "
"tatiyo sūriyo pātubhavati."
msgstr ""
"There comes a time when, after a very long period has passed, a third sun "
"appears."

msgctxt "an7.66:5.2"
msgid ""
"Tatiyassa, bhikkhave, sūriyassa pātubhāvā yā kāci mahānadiyo, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "When this happens, the great rivers—"

msgctxt "an7.66:5.3"
msgid ""
"gaṅgā, yamunā, aciravatī, sarabhū, mahī, tā ussussanti visussanti, na "
"bhavanti."
msgstr ""
"the Ganges, Yamunā, Aciravatī, Sarabhū, and Mahī—wither away and dry up, and "
"are no more."

msgctxt "an7.66:5.4"
msgid "Evaṃ aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā … pe …"
msgstr "So impermanent are conditions …"

msgctxt "an7.66:5.5"
msgid "alaṃ vimuccituṃ. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an7.66:6.1"
msgid ""
"Hoti kho so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno accayena "
"catuttho sūriyo pātubhavati."
msgstr ""
"There comes a time when, after a very long period has passed, a fourth sun "
"appears."

msgctxt "an7.66:6.2"
msgid ""
"Catutthassa, bhikkhave, sūriyassa pātubhāvā ye te mahāsarā yato imā "
"mahānadiyo pavattanti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "When this happens, the great lakes from which the rivers originate—"

msgctxt "an7.66:6.3"
msgid ""
"anotattā, sīhapapātā, rathakārā, kaṇṇamuṇḍā, kuṇālā, chaddantā, mandākiniyā, "
"tā ussussanti visussanti, na bhavanti."
msgstr ""
"the Anotattā, Sīhapapātā, Rathakārā, Kaṇṇamuṇḍā, Kuṇālā, Chaddantā, and "
"Mandākinī—wither away and dry up, and are no more."

msgctxt "an7.66:6.4"
msgid "Evaṃ aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā … pe …"
msgstr "So impermanent are conditions …"

msgctxt "an7.66:6.5"
msgid "alaṃ vimuccituṃ. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.102"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an7.66:7.1"
msgid ""
"Hoti kho so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno accayena "
"pañcamo sūriyo pātubhavati."
msgstr ""
"There comes a time when, after a very long period has passed, a fifth sun "
"appears."

msgctxt "an7.66:7.2"
msgid ""
"Pañcamassa, bhikkhave, sūriyassa pātubhāvā yojanasatikānipi mahāsamudde "
"udakāni ogacchanti, dviyojanasatikānipi mahāsamudde udakāni ogacchanti, "
"tiyojanasatikānipi, catuyojanasatikānipi, pañcayojanasatikānipi, "
"chayojanasatikānipi, sattayojanasatikānipi mahāsamudde udakāni ogacchanti;"
msgstr ""
"When this happens, the water in the ocean sinks by a hundred leagues. It "
"sinks by two, three, four, five, six, or even seven hundred leagues."

msgctxt "an7.66:7.3"
msgid ""
"sattatālampi mahāsamudde udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, chatālampi, pañcatālampi, "
"catutālampi, titālampi, dvitālampi, tālamattampi mahāsamudde udakaṃ saṇṭhāti;"
msgstr ""
"The water that remains in the ocean is only seven palm trees deep. It’s six, "
"five, four, three, two, or even one palm tree deep."

#. VAR: porisampi → porisamattampi (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.66:7.4"
msgid ""
"sattaporisampi mahāsamudde udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, chaporisampi, pañcaporisampi, "
"catuporisampi, tiporisampi, dviporisampi, porisampi, aḍḍhaporisampi, "
"kaṭimattampi, jaṇṇukāmattampi, gopphakamattampi mahāsamudde udakaṃ saṇṭhāti."
msgstr ""
"The water that remains in the ocean is only seven fathoms deep. It’s six, "
"five, four, three, two, one or even half a fathom deep. It’s waist high, "
"knee high, or even ankle high."

#. VAR: tattha gopadesu → gopphakapadesesu (mr)
msgctxt "an7.66:7.5"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, saradasamaye thullaphusitake deve vassante tattha "
"tattha gopadesu udakāni ṭhitāni honti;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like the time in the autumn, when the rain falls heavily and water "
"remains here and there in the cow’s hoofprints."

#. VAR: gopphakamattāni → gopadamattāni (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.66:7.6"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tattha tattha gopphakamattāni mahāsamudde udakāni "
"ṭhitāni honti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, water in the ocean remains here and there in puddles like "
"cow’s hoofprints."

msgctxt "an7.66:7.7"
msgid ""
"Pañcamassa, bhikkhave, sūriyassa pātubhāvā aṅgulipabbamattampi mahāsamudde "
"udakaṃ na hoti."
msgstr ""
"When the fifth sun appears there’s not even enough water in the great ocean "
"to wet a toe-joint."

msgctxt "an7.66:7.8"
msgid "Evaṃ aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā … pe …"
msgstr "So impermanent are conditions …"

msgctxt "an7.66:7.9"
msgid "alaṃ vimuccituṃ. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an7.66:8.1"
msgid ""
"Hoti kho so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno accayena "
"chaṭṭho sūriyo pātubhavati."
msgstr ""
"There comes a time when, after a very long period has passed, a sixth sun "
"appears."

#. VAR: dhūmāyanti sandhūmāyanti sampadhūmāyanti → dhūpāyanti sandhūpāyanti sampadhūpāyanti (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.66:8.2"
msgid ""
"Chaṭṭhassa, bhikkhave, sūriyassa pātubhāvā ayañca mahāpathavī sineru ca "
"pabbatarājā dhūmāyanti sandhūmāyanti sampadhūmāyanti."
msgstr ""
"When this happens, this great earth and Sineru the king of mountains smoke "
"and smolder and give off fumes."

#. VAR: ālepito → ālimpito (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.66:8.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kumbhakārapāko ālepito paṭhamaṃ dhūmeti sandhūmeti "
"sampadhūmeti;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like when a potter’s kiln is first kindled, and it smokes and smolders "
"and gives off fumes."

msgctxt "an7.66:8.4"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, chaṭṭhassa sūriyassa pātubhāvā ayañca mahāpathavī "
"sineru ca pabbatarājā dhūmāyanti sandhūmāyanti sampadhūmāyanti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, this great earth and Sineru the king of mountains smoke and "
"smolder and give off fumes."

msgctxt "an7.66:8.5"
msgid "Evaṃ aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā … pe …"
msgstr "So impermanent are conditions …"

msgctxt "an7.66:8.6"
msgid "alaṃ vimuccituṃ. (6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.103"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an7.66:9.1"
msgid ""
"Hoti kho so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno accayena "
"sattamo sūriyo pātubhavati."
msgstr ""
"There comes a time when, after a very long period has passed, a seventh sun "
"appears."

msgctxt "an7.66:9.2"
msgid ""
"Sattamassa, bhikkhave, sūriyassa pātubhāvā ayañca mahāpathavī sineru ca "
"pabbatarājā ādippanti pajjalanti ekajālā bhavanti."
msgstr ""
"When this happens, this great earth and Sineru the king of mountains erupt "
"in one burning mass of fire."

msgctxt "an7.66:9.3"
msgid ""
"Imissā ca, bhikkhave, mahāpathaviyā sinerussa ca pabbatarājassa jhāyamānānaṃ "
"dayhamānānaṃ acci vātena khittā yāva brahmalokāpi gacchati."
msgstr ""
"And as they blaze and burn the flames are swept by the wind as far as the "
"Brahmā realm."

msgctxt "an7.66:9.4"
msgid ""
"Sinerussa, bhikkhave, pabbatarājassa jhāyamānassa dayhamānassa "
"vinassamānassa mahatā tejokhandhena abhibhūtassa yojanasatikānipi kūṭāni "
"palujjanti dviyojanasatikānipi, tiyojanasatikānipi, catuyojanasatikānipi, "
"pañcayojanasatikānipi kūṭāni palujjanti."
msgstr ""
"Sineru the king of mountains blazes and burns, crumbling as it’s overcome by "
"the great heat. And meanwhile, mountain peaks a hundred leagues high, or "
"two, three, four, or five hundred leagues high disintegrate as they burn."

msgctxt "an7.66:9.5"
msgid ""
"Imissā ca, bhikkhave, mahāpathaviyā sinerussa ca pabbatarājassa jhāyamānānaṃ "
"dayhamānānaṃ neva chārikā paññāyati na masi."
msgstr ""
"And when the great earth and Sineru the king of mountains blaze and burn, no "
"soot or ash is found."

msgctxt "an7.66:9.6"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, sappissa vā telassa vā jhāyamānassa dayhamānassa neva "
"chārikā paññāyati na masi;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like when ghee or oil blaze and burn, and neither ashes nor soot are "
"found."

msgctxt "an7.66:9.7"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, imissā ca mahāpathaviyā sinerussa ca pabbatarājassa "
"jhāyamānānaṃ dayhamānānaṃ neva chārikā paññāyati na masi."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when the great earth and Sineru the king of mountains blaze "
"and burn, no soot or ash is found."

msgctxt "an7.66:9.8"
msgid "Evaṃ aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā;"
msgstr "So impermanent are conditions,"

msgctxt "an7.66:9.9"
msgid "evaṃ adhuvā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā;"
msgstr "so unstable are conditions,"

msgctxt "an7.66:9.10"
msgid "evaṃ anassāsikā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā."
msgstr "so unreliable are conditions."

msgctxt "an7.66:9.11"
msgid ""
"Yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, alameva sabbasaṅkhāresu nibbindituṃ alaṃ virajjituṃ "
"alaṃ vimuccituṃ. (7)"
msgstr ""
"This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and "
"freed regarding all conditions."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an7.66:10.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ko mantā ko saddhātā:"
msgstr "Mendicants, who would ever think or believe that"

msgctxt "an7.66:10.2"
msgid ""
"‘ayañca pathavī sineru ca pabbatarājā dayhissanti vinassissanti, na "
"bhavissantī’ti aññatra diṭṭhapadehi?"
msgstr ""
"this earth and Sineru, king of mountains, will burn and crumble and be no "
"more, except for one who has seen the truth?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.104"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an7.66:11.1"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, sunetto nāma satthā ahosi titthakaro kāmesu vītarāgo."
msgstr ""
"Once upon a time, there was a Teacher called Sunetta. He was a religious "
"founder and was free of sensual desire."

msgctxt "an7.66:11.2"
msgid "Sunettassa kho pana, bhikkhave, satthuno anekāni sāvakasatāni ahesuṃ."
msgstr "He had many hundreds of disciples."

msgctxt "an7.66:11.3"
msgid ""
"Sunetto, bhikkhave, satthā sāvakānaṃ brahmalokasahabyatāya dhammaṃ desesi."
msgstr "He taught them the path to rebirth in the company of Brahmā."

msgctxt "an7.66:11.4"
msgid ""
"Ye kho pana, bhikkhave, sunettassa satthuno brahmalokasahabyatāya dhammaṃ "
"desentassa sabbena sabbaṃ sāsanaṃ ājāniṃsu te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"sugatiṃ brahmalokaṃ upapajjiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Those who totally understood Sunetta’s teachings were—when their body broke "
"up, after death—reborn in a good place, the company of Brahmā."

msgctxt "an7.66:11.5"
msgid ""
"Ye na sabbena sabbaṃ sāsanaṃ ājāniṃsu te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"appekacce paranimmitavasavattīnaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjiṃsu, appekacce "
"nimmānaratīnaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjiṃsu, appekacce tusitānaṃ devānaṃ "
"sahabyataṃ upapajjiṃsu, appekacce yāmānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjiṃsu, "
"appekacce tāvatiṃsānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjiṃsu, appekacce "
"cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjiṃsu, appekacce "
"khattiyamahāsālānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjiṃsu, appekacce brāhmaṇamahāsālānaṃ "
"sahabyataṃ upapajjiṃsu, appekacce gahapatimahāsālānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Of those who didn’t totally understand Sunetta’s teachings, some—when their "
"body broke up, after death—were reborn in the company of the Gods Who "
"Control the Creations of Others. Some were reborn in the company of the Gods "
"Who Love to Create, some with the Joyful Gods, some with the Gods of Yama, "
"some with the Gods of the Thirty-Three, and some with the Gods of the Four "
"Great Kings. Some were reborn in the company of well-to-do aristocrats or "
"brahmins or householders."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an7.66:12.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sunettassa satthuno etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then the Teacher Sunetta thought:"

# BB (original edition) has a typo here, the close quote is omitted.
#. VAR: uttari mettaṃ → uttariṃ mettaṃ (s2, s3, pts1) | uttari maggaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an7.66:12.2"
msgid ""
"‘na kho metaṃ patirūpaṃ yohaṃ sāvakānaṃ samasamagatiyo assaṃ abhisamparāyaṃ, "
"yannūnāhaṃ uttari mettaṃ bhāveyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s not proper for me to be reborn in the next life in exactly the same "
"place as my disciples. Why don’t I further develop love?’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.105"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
#. VAR: mettaṃ cittaṃ → mettacittaṃ (s2, s3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.66:13.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, sunetto satthā satta vassāni mettaṃ cittaṃ bhāvesi."
msgstr "Then Sunetta developed love for seven years."

#. VAR: mettaṃ cittaṃ → mettacittaṃ (s2, s3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.66:13.2"
msgid ""
"Satta vassāni mettaṃ cittaṃ bhāvetvā satta saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe nayimaṃ "
"lokaṃ punarāgamāsi."
msgstr ""
"Having done so he did not return to this world for seven eons of cosmic "
"expansion and contraction."

msgctxt "an7.66:13.3"
msgid "Saṃvaṭṭamāne sudaṃ, bhikkhave, loke ābhassarūpago hoti."
msgstr "As the cosmos contracted he went to the realm of streaming radiance."

msgctxt "an7.66:13.4"
msgid "Vivaṭṭamāne loke suññaṃ brahmavimānaṃ upapajjati."
msgstr "As it expanded he was reborn in an empty mansion of Brahmā."

msgctxt "an7.66:13.5"
msgid ""
"Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, brahmā hoti mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto "
"aññadatthudaso vasavattī."
msgstr ""
"There he was Brahmā, the Great Brahmā, the undefeated, the champion, the "
"universal seer, the wielder of power."

msgctxt "an7.66:13.6"
msgid "Chattiṃsakkhattuṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, sakko ahosi devānamindo."
msgstr "He was Sakka, lord of gods, thirty-six times."

msgctxt "an7.66:13.7"
msgid ""
"Anekasatakkhattuṃ rājā ahosi cakkavattī dhammiko dhammarājā cāturanto "
"vijitāvī janapadatthāvariyappatto sattaratanasamannāgato."
msgstr ""
"Many hundreds of times he was a king, a wheel-turning monarch, a just and "
"principled king. His dominion extended to all four sides, he achieved "
"stability in the country, and he possessed the seven treasures."

msgctxt "an7.66:13.8"
msgid ""
"Parosahassaṃ kho panassa puttā ahesuṃ sūrā vīraṅgarūpā parasenappamaddanā."
msgstr ""
"He had over a thousand sons who were valiant and heroic, crushing the armies "
"of his enemies."

msgctxt "an7.66:13.9"
msgid ""
"So imaṃ pathaviṃ sāgarapariyantaṃ adaṇḍena asatthena dhammena abhivijiya "
"ajjhāvasi."
msgstr ""
"After conquering this land girt by sea, he reigned by principle, without rod "
"or sword."

msgctxt "an7.66:13.10"
msgid ""
"So hi nāma, bhikkhave, sunetto satthā evaṃ dīghāyuko samāno evaṃ "
"ciraṭṭhitiko aparimutto ahosi:"
msgstr "Yet even though Sunetta lived so long, he was not exempt from"

msgctxt "an7.66:13.11"
msgid ""
"‘jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, "
"aparimutto dukkhasmā’ti vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"rebirth, old age, and death. He was not exempt from sorrow, lamentation, "
"pain, dejection, and despair, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.106"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an7.66:14.1"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an7.66:14.2"
msgid "Catunnaṃ dhammānaṃ ananubodhā appaṭivedhā."
msgstr "Because of not understanding and not comprehending four things."

msgctxt "an7.66:14.3"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an7.66:14.4"
msgid ""
"Ariyassa, bhikkhave, sīlassa ananubodhā appaṭivedhā, ariyassa samādhissa "
"ananubodhā appaṭivedhā, ariyāya paññāya ananubodhā appaṭivedhā, ariyāya "
"vimuttiyā ananubodhā appaṭivedhā."
msgstr "Noble ethics, immersion, wisdom, and freedom."

msgctxt "an7.66:14.5"
msgid ""
"Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyaṃ sīlaṃ anubuddhaṃ paṭividdhaṃ, ariyo samādhi "
"anubodho paṭividdho, ariyā paññā anubodhā paṭividdhā, ariyā vimutti anubodhā "
"paṭividdhā, ucchinnā bhavataṇhā, khīṇā bhavanetti, natthi dāni punabbhavo”ti."
msgstr ""
"These noble ethics, immersion, wisdom, and freedom have been understood and "
"comprehended. Craving for continued existence has been cut off; the "
"attachment to continued existence is ended; now there are no more future "
"lives.”"

msgctxt "an7.66:14.6"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "an7.66:14.7"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an7.66:15.1"
msgid "“Sīlaṃ samādhi paññā ca,"
msgstr "“Ethics, immersion, and wisdom,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.66:15.2"
msgid "vimutti ca anuttarā;"
msgstr "and the supreme freedom:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.66:15.3"
msgid "Anubuddhā ime dhammā,"
msgstr "these things have been understood"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.66:15.4"
msgid "gotamena yasassinā."
msgstr "by Gotama the renowned."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an7.66:16.1"
msgid "Iti buddho abhiññāya,"
msgstr "And so the Buddha, having insight,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.66:16.2"
msgid "dhammamakkhāsi bhikkhunaṃ;"
msgstr "explained this teaching to the mendicants."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.66:16.3"
msgid "Dukkhassantakaro satthā,"
msgstr "The Teacher has made an end of suffering;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.66:16.4"
msgid "cakkhumā parinibbuto”ti."
msgstr "seeing clearly, he is extinguished.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.66:16.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
